reviews.review_text: Great show! I have a great disc of this show and I use 3/1/69 I as filler
My First "Show" It is truly cool to have a document of this!!!

1/17/79 make up show Reviewer: Street Pig - 4.00 out of 5 stars4.00 out of 5 stars4.00 out of 5 stars4.00 out of 5 stars - July 7, 2005
Subject: 11.25 Cancellation
I remember the lights were off, we we were "on" and Bobby & Mickey coming out with the news of Jer on the respirator, i cannot recall a single boo nor anything said negative whatsoever, a lot of "Man I hope Jer will be alright" We went up to a bar on the corner and listen to an impromptu Elvis impersonator while we slammed down Balantine XXX Ale. The make-up show started with a Shakedown which was a "I told ya I'll be back" reassurance for us Jersey Freaks, this and the Springfield 1-15th were great times
Huh? Is this really necessary? *rolls eyes*

Happy Camper I was 15 and had my ticket stolen by some hoods a couple weeks before this show.  I called the house, told them my sob story and they said I could pick one up at will call.  My mom dropped me off and I had my first experience of trying to get into a Dead show dosed with no ticket!  Suddenly, everyone was leaving the building and I scored an 11th row center ticket from some head who could not return for the make up.  Next, I see the crew I suspected of breaking into my room and stealing my ticket during a party.  I laughed so hard I thought I'd die.  I boarded the southbound train the only happy head to see them cancel.  My mom picked me up at the station just as I was coming down and I remember having a blast playing foosball with my older brothers friends debating Springsteen vs. Jerry.  The make up on 1-17-79 was my 2nd show and being up front blew mind. The dbag that stole my ticket got busted for weed before the show and his friends were in the nose bleeds. Karma.

Thus is born the Jan 1979 tour I was there for this. It is true that no one seemed upset about the situation. Rather people were concerned for Jerry's health.

The upside was an outstanding tour in Jan of 79.
Was able to go both Philly, MSG and Nassau shows as well as the make up for this show. 1/10/79 was the return of Dark Star to the east coast and the St. Stephen is outstanding.

The funny part was that the make up show for this cancellation was my least favorite show of the Jan 79 tour!
